title: Sheikh Jassim expected to make a second bid for Manchester United within 10 days
description: Sheikh Jassim bin Hamad al Thani will make a second bid for Manchester United within 10 days after his representatives visited the Premier League club.

title: 'Russian troops guarantee our safety': How public opinion in breakaway Moldova region favours the east
description: On the edge of Europe is a pocket of pro-Russian support which has been under close watch since the outbreak of war in Ukraine.

title: Chaos in French parliament as Macron bypasses vote and forces through controversial pensions bill
description: There have been rare chaotic scenes in the French parliament as President Emmanuel Macron used special powers to push through an unpopular pensions bill which aims to raise the retirement age from 62 to 64.

title: FIFA confirms no Saudi deal for Women's World Cup after human rights backlash
description: FIFA President Gianni Infantino has confirmed that Saudi Arabia's government tourism agency will not now be a Women's World Cup sponsor.

title: European Central Bank hikes interest rates despite market turmoil
description: The European Central Bank (ECB) has maintained its fight against inflation and imposed a large set of interest rate hikes despite financial market turmoil.

title: Poland to send at least four MiG-29 fighter jets to Ukraine
description: Poland is to send Ukraine four MiG-29 fighter jets in the coming days, it has been announced, with more to follow later.

title: Farmers' protest party enjoys big win in Dutch provincial elections
description: A farmers' protest party has shaken up the political landscape in the Netherlands as it emerges as the big winner in provincial elections, posing a big challenge the prime minister.

title: Fans clash with police before Champions League match in Naples
description: Hundreds of Eintracht Frankfurt fans clashed with police in violent scenes in Naples last night, despite being banned from the second leg of their Champions League tie against Napoli.

title: Chinese ChatGPT rival disappoints - but does have a cute name
description: The battle of the AI chatbots has stepped up a notch after Chinese search giant Baidu unveiled its much-anticipated rival to ChatGPT.

title: Video shows moment Russian fighter jet intercepts US drone
description: The US Air Force has released video said to show a Russian jet intercepting an American drone and dumping fuel in its path over the Black Sea.

title: About 2.5 tonnes of uranium goes missing in war-torn Libya
description: Some 2.5 tonnes of natural uranium stored in a site in war-torn Libya has gone missing, the United Nations nuclear watchdog said, raising safety and proliferation concerns.

title: Justin Bieber shares health update after face paralysis forced him to cancel world tour
description: Justin Bieber has shared a video of him flashing a smile - an inconsequential move for most stars, but huge for him considering facial paralysis forced the singer to cancel his world tour.

title: 'Read a history book': DUP leader's riposte to Chuck Schumer amid Brexit jostling in Washington
description: The DUP leader Sir Jeffrey Donaldson has said that Chuck Schumer needs to read some history books, after the US Senate majority leader urged the DUP to go back into Stormont.

title: Chancellor 'welcomes' Credit Suisse £44.5bn lifeline as shares bounce back
description: Chancellor Jeremy Hunt has "welcomed" the Swiss central bank's decision to give Credit Suisse a lifeline of 50bn Swiss francs (£44.5bn).

title: Credit Suisse secures £44.5bn lifeline amid fears of global financial crisis
description: Credit Suisse has said it will borrow up to 50bn Swiss francs (£44.5bn) from the Swiss central bank to shore up its liquidity.
